OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FAn 86-year-old woman has been
OL,7,Fconvicted of a driving offence after
OL,8,Fmistakenly getting a letter wrong on
OL,9,Fcar insurance papers.
OL,11,FThe pensioner, from York, believed she
OL,12,Fwas complying with the law after
OL,13,Fpaying for a year's worth of cover for
OL,14,Fher Suzuki Splash car with Swinton
OL,15,FInsurance.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FBut she was sent a letter from the
OL,7,FDVLA saying she was being prosecuted
OL,8,Ffor keeping a vehicle without
OL,9,Finsurance after writing that her
OL,10,Fnumber plate contained an "F" instead
OL,11,Fof an "S".
OL,13,FThe octogenarian, who has not been
OL,14,Fnamed, wrote to magistrates setting
OL,15,Fout the mistake, while her niece also
OL,16,Fpenned a letter explaining that the
OL,17,Ffamily was now stepping in to help as
OL,18,Fthey "did not know it had got to the
OL,19,Fstage where she can't cope".
OL,26,@zD@FOU{D@[O]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FDespite the letters, the pensioner was
OL,7,Fconvicted of a crime in the Single
OL,8,FJustice Procedure, a controversial
OL,9,Ffast-track court process where
OL,10,Fmagistrates hand out convictions and
OL,11,Fpunishments in private hearings.
OL,13,FShe was sentenced to a three-month
OL,14,Fconditional discharge instead of a
OL,15,Ffine, but also ordered to pay a #26
OL,16,Fvictim surcharge.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FAccording to the Press Association,
OL,7,Fthe DVLA said it would now contact the
OL,8,Fwoman to check her insurance paperwork
OL,9,Fand would seek to have the conviction
OL,10,Foverturned if the typo was to blame.
OL,12,FThe pensioner faced prosecution after
OL,13,Fit was said her car was uninsured on 6
OL,14,FFebruary 2026.
OL,16,FReplying to the Single Justice
OL,17,FProcedure notice, she wrote: "I
OL,18,Funderstood my car was fully insured
OL,19,Fwith Swinton Insurance, from 1 April
OL,20,F2025 to 31 March 2026.
OL,26,@yD@^OU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,F"I did not notice the registration
OL,7,Fprinted wrongly.
OL,9,F"Had an F instead of an S."
OL,11,FHer niece also sent in a letter,
OL,12,Fexplaining: "All the paperwork for
OL,13,Finsurance has been found to be one
OL,14,Fletter incorrect.
OL,16,F"No-one had picked up on this.
OL,18,F"I am now helping her with her
OL,19,Fpaperwork as we (the family) did not
OL,20,Fknow it had got to the stage where she
OL,21,Fcan't cope.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@AOUqD@[O]tD@MOUxD@AOUzD@AOU
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,F"She has tried to complete the form as
OL,7,Fbest as possible."
OL,9,FThe Single Justice Procedure was
OL,10,Finvented in 2015 as a cheaper way of
OL,11,Fhandling low-level criminal cases,
OL,12,Fallowing a magistrate sitting alone in
OL,13,Fprivate to take decisions instead of
OL,14,Fthree magistrates deliberating
OL,15,Ftogether in open court.
OL,17,FCases are decided based on written
OL,18,Fevidence alone, and there is no
OL,19,Fprosecutor present to see the
OL,20,Fmitigation and other correspondence
OL,21,Fsent in by the defendant.
OL,26,@nD@AOUoD@RO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FThe design of the fast-track process
OL,7,Fmeans prosecutors are unable to review
OL,8,Fnew evidence that has come to light,
OL,9,For take a decision to withdraw a case
OL,10,Fthat is no longer in the public
OL,11,Finterest.
OL,13,FIn the pensioner's case, David
OL,14,FPollard, a magistrate sitting at
OL,15,FTeesside Magistrates' Court, opted to
OL,16,Faccept the written guilty plea and
OL,17,Fimpose a conviction, rather than
OL,18,Fasking the DVLA to do further checks
OL,19,Fon the public interest in the
OL,20,Fprosecution.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FThe Labour Government conducted a
OL,7,Fconsultation on possible changes to
OL,8,Fthe Single Justice Procedure system
OL,9,Fbetween March and May last year, after
OL,10,Fa string of media revelations about
OL,11,Fharsh convictions and injustices
OL,12,Finvolving elderly and vulnerable
OL,13,Fpeople.
OL,15,FNo plan for change has emerged since
OL,16,Fthe end of the consultation nearly a
OL,17,Fyear ago.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/10
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,369,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F368A1776859865
OL,3,C86-year-old who mixed up 'f' and 's'
OL,4,Con insurance form convicted
OL,6,FHowever the Lady Chief Justice
OL,7,FBaroness Carr revealed at her annual
OL,8,Fpress conference in March that Lord
OL,9,FJustice Green, the Senior Presiding
OL,10,FJudge for England and Wales, is
OL,11,Fleading a "nuts and bolts audit" of
OL,12,Fthe Single Justice Procedure.
OL,14,FA working group, comprising of judges,
OL,15,Fmagistrates, and justice officials,
OL,16,F"will soon conclude" the audit, the
OL,17,FJudicial Office said, with
OL,18,Frecommendations set to go to the
OL,19,FInterim Magistrates Executive Board.
OL,26,@sD@KOUsD@`O]xD@AOUxD@TO]
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/10
